Record an agent session inside a PTY (SRS FR-1)

Usage: hh run [OPTIONS] -- <COMMAND>...

Arguments:
  <COMMAND>...  The command to run and its arguments, after `--`

Options:
      --record-input       Record user keystrokes (off by default; keystrokes may contain secrets — SRS NFR-4)
      --adapter <ADAPTER>  Force an adapter rather than auto-detecting (`claude-code`, `claude-desktop`, `codex-cli`, `gemini-cli`)
  -h, --help               Print help

Example:
  hh run -- claude
  hh run --record-input -- python3 my_agent.py
